column5: Just a heads up for folks just picked up a Plano softsider at Canadian Tire for 50% off, includes 4 prolatch utility boxes, 2 zip up outside pockets - $14.
do u have a link to which model it is? I TRIED LOOKING , CHeapest i found was 24$
That's probably the one going on sale.  The sale is for this coming week starting on 27th... 50% off, $12.49
They had them on sale for $9 the last time if it's the blue one with yellow piping and opens on the top,

Can't find the exact one on the Plano site but here is the one almost identical. Except the one on sale has 2 zip up outside pockets and one mesh pocket   Check under the softsider series  3364-00  SOFTSIDERâ„¢ GEAR BAG  http://www.planomolding.com/tackle/products.asp

yeah, that's it.   I thought it might  be the one below it until i saw the dimensions.  The other one is much larger the model you guessed was the one for $9 for sure.    A friend bought 4 of them, i didn't get any thinking they were too small and soon regretted it.

I bought a couple, they hold 4 trays each and I find it easier to organize my tackle for species and then by lure. I can carry everything I need for bass in one bag, same for walleye, etc., usually three trays and the extra room for soft plastics.
I picked one up last year and you just can't enough of these little guys.  I have mine sorted out by species.  Handy that way!
